Thanks for the answer. Indeed Ruby in general has the limitations inherent to its &quot;non functional&quot; nature. However regarding 2) Enumeration can now (in ruby 2.0) be lazy and thus take each item one after the other through the whole chain.<p>(1..Float::INFINITY).lazy.map{|a| p a; a*10}.map{|a| p a+1}
# => 1 11 2 21 etc...<p>So it can work with streams & so on... 
But I know (from a Jessica Kerr presentation) it also has limitations there.
